Quote:  The fishermen who go out to the 100-150-fathom water off [Otago] frequently catch ... a huge groper, which they call `bass groper', and which seems to be specifically distinct from the ordinary hapuka. They say it is common off Wellington, and is there known as `black bass'. [216] ... I ... made inquiries of local [Wellington] fish-merchants, and learned that ... from Kaikoura a large groper was occasionally received, and was called a `bass' ...
Notes:  Waite

